	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Do any games use tile/sprite overlap for more colors?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think I've seen some Genesis games that overlay tiles or overlap sprites in order to fake objects with more than 16 colors.
<br />
<br />I don't think I've seen this in NES games.  Why not?  Or, am I missing the instances where they do?
<br />
<br />I could at least see tile/sprite combinations happening as coarse movement was more acceptable back then.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
